<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06213217 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06213217 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  ALAMEDA; COUNTY; EMPLOYMENT; DECREASE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Alameda County is giving 24 furloughed sheriff's deputies and technicians twomore weeks of work while officials decide whether to ax their jobs for good.;   Supervisors agreed Tuesday to spend $43,000 to keep the workers on thepayroll until Aug. 13. The board is slated to vote then on a proposal to givethe sheriff's department $1 million more to pay the deputies through the year.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  DEPUTIES FACING LAYOFFS GET SMALL REPRIEVE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Sunday was to have been the deputies' last day of work. An additional 22sheriff's employees still will be laid off as part of $44 million in cuts tothe county budget.;    &quot;It's really demoralizing our whole organization,&quot; saidSheriff Charles Plummer, who is being forced to close one floor of the NorthCounty Jail in Oakland.;    By temporarily saving 24 jobs, Plummer said, he'llbe able to keep all but one of the 15 housing units open at Santa Rita Jail inDublin. Otherwise, he would have closed three inmate &quot;pods.&quot;;    To raise the$1 million for the sheriff, the board may suspend a $550 annual bonus given tothe county's 2,300 managers.;    Also on Aug. 13, the board will get detailson a long-awaited survey of management fat in county government.;    Lastweek, the board gave Plummer an additional $2.4 million after learning thatthe state budget would provide the county with an unexpected $12.8 million.;   In other action Tuesday, the board approved new rates for emergency medicalservices countywide. In Fremont, property owners will pay $25.54 annually --up from the current $19.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  ABBY COHN, Mercury News Oakland Bureau  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Alameda County/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910731  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  252  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday July 31, 199100213217,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>